3 §3386.2. Addictive Disorder Regulatory Authority
4 A. The legislature hereby finds it appropriate that the responsibility and
5 authority to regulate the practice of addictive disorder treatment, and prevention, and
6 peer support shall be exercised by a licensing board created for that purpose. It is
7 the intent of the legislature that a single authority issue and recognize
8 credentials for addictive disorder counseling, prevention, and peer support
9 professionals in Louisiana, and that such authority shall be the Addictive
10 Disorder Regulatory Authority.
11 B. The Addictive Disorder Regulatory Authority (ADRA) is hereby created
12 within the Louisiana Department of Health. The ADRA shall be governed by a board
13 of directors, referred to hereafter in this Chapter as the "board", consisting of eight
14 eleven voting members, composed of one member appointed by the secretary of
15 the Louisiana Department of Health to represent the office of behavioral health
16 and ten members all of whom shall be appointed by the governor, subject to Senate
17 confirmation, as follows:
